 Lusikisiki police and the Bizana stock theft unit recovered 18 sheep at an abandoned homestead at Candlovu Location on Thursday. According to police spokesperson, Captain Edith Mjoko, 44 sheep were reported stolen at a kraal at Mpendla Location. “All the recovered sheep were locked inside a flat. They were all identified by the complainant and no arrest has been made yet,” she added. “Twenty-six sheep are still missing and police working around the clock to recover the outstanding stock.”  